					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: The Bacon Boom</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-08T17:06:45+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 8, 2014 1:06 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 8, 2014 1:06 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/today-in-small-business-the-bacon-boom/" data-title="Today in Small Business: The Bacon Boom" data-description="The &quot;most bountiful&quot; holiday season in three years? The most innovative cities in America. Did Comcast retaliate against an unhappy customer by getting him fired?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Home prices <a href="//www.calculatedriskblog.com/2014/10/corelogic-house-prices-up-64-year-over.html?">were up</a> 6.4 percent year over year in August.</li>
<li>Heating costs are <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/business/energy-environment/us-consumer-energy-costs-expected-to-decline-this-winter.html">expected to decline</a> this winter.</li>
<li>Job openings <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/07/us-usa-economy-vacancies-idUSKCN0HW1D420141007?f">hit their highest level</a> since 2001.</li>
<li>Although 77 percent of small businesses &#8220;feel successful,&#8221; <a href="//www.businesswire.com/news/home/20141007005286/en/Hedging-Bets-Small-Business-Owners-Feel-Successful#.VDRrwvldVgs">most are still not hiring</a>.</li>
<li>A former director of the Office of Management and Budget explains <a href="//www.bloombergview.com/articles/2014-10-07/what-tattoos-tell-us-about-the-economy">what tattoos tell us</a> about the economy.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retailing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wealthier shoppers are likely to drive &#8220;<a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/07/us-usa-retail-holidays-idUSKCN0HW1BV20141007">the most bountiful</a>&#8221; holiday season in three years.</li>
<li>Amazon says that<a href="//finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-expands-seller-holiday-deals-110300308.html"> top deals from its small-business sellers</a> will now be featured on holiday deal pages.</li>
<li>A<a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/realestate/commercial/in-depths-of-columbus-circle-a-retail-hub-blooms.html"> retail hub blooms</a> at a New York subway stop.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Here is why the <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-10-06/bacon-why-americas-favorite-food-mania-happened">bacon boom</a> was no accident.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-89190"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A star-studded start-up vows to make <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/highfive-launch-2014-10?">conference calls</a> easier.</li>
<li>Here is how start-ups <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/10/07/smallbusiness/dc-startups/index.html">are tackling</a> Washington&#8217;s poverty.</li>
<li>If youâre thinking of <a href="//www.dexmedia.com/blog/franchises-sba-loan-default-may-stars/">buying a franchise</a> be careful: Some chains are more prone to loan defaults than others.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A chief executive says <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/237879">the smart move</a> for growing companies is to always be recruiting talent.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here are a few reasons the <a href="//www.smallbizlabs.com/2014/10/why-the-self-employed-often-flourish-.html">self-employed flourish</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/10/7/6939057/walmart-drops-insurance-good-news">the positive side</a> of tens of thousands of Walmart workers&#8217; loss of health coverage.</li>
<li>More than a dozen high-end restaurants in Los Angeles are levying a <a href="//www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-restaurant-healthcare-surcharge-20141007-story.html#page=1">3 percent customer surcharge</a> to cover their employeesâ medical insurance.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Customer Service</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Did Comcast <a href="//m.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/morning_roundup/2014/10/comcast-got-unhappy-customer-fired-from-his-job.html">retaliate against an unhappy customer</a> by getting him fired?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A new book from a professor of management explores how <a href="//blogs.hbr.org/2014/10/what-successful-work-and-life-integration-looks-like/">successful people</a> balance their professional and personal lives.</li>
<li>Here is why optimists <a href="//elitedaily.com/life/culture/optimists-actually-unhappier-might-think/786578/">are actually unhappier</a> than pessimists.</li>
<li>These are the <a href="//theselfemployed.com/find_work/the-pros-and-cons-of-working-with-family/">pros and cons</a> of working with family members.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s how Firestone <a href="//www.npr.org/blogs/goatsandsoda/2014/10/06/354054915/firestone-did-what-governments-have-not-stopped-ebola-in-its-tracks">did a better job</a> than any government at stopping Ebola.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This infographic reveals <a href="//www.coolinfographics.com/blog/2014/10/6/the-scary-truth-about-your-passwords-an-analysis-of-the-gmai.html?">the scary truth</a> about your weak password.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Boeing predicts that global air cargo traffic <a href="//www.industryweek.com/transportation/global-air-cargo-traffic-double-20-years">will double</a> in the next 20 years.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This fall, there is a battle in the San Francisco Bay Area <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/us/berkeley-officials-outspent-but-optimistic-in-battle-over-soda-tax.html">over a soda tax</a>.</li>
<li>A small Illinois town <a href="//www.mbtmag.com/news/2014/10/town-creates-80-percent-all-canned-pumpkin-consumed-us">creates 80 percent</a> of the canned pumpkin consumed in the United States.</li>
<li>A <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/Environment/Latest-News-Wires/2014/1007/Dead-bear-cub-found-in-Central-Park">dead bear cub</a> is found in Central Park.</li>
<li>These are the <a href="//money.cnn.com/gallery/technology/2014/10/07/most-innovative-cities/index.html">most innovative cities</a> in America.</li>
<li>Four bars and nightclubs in Fresno, Calif., <a href="//www.kmph.com/story/26720495/navy-sailors-banned-from-fresno-nightclubs">are off limits</a> to Navy sailors.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Should we ban flights from countries <a href="//www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/ban-flights-countries-ebola-outbreaks">with Ebola outbreaks</a>?</li>
<li>A New Zealand cafe has <a href="//www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/cafe-apologises-for-making-sick-joke-about-killing-of-pistorius-girlfriend-steenkamp-114100700231_1.html">reportedly issued</a> an apology for joking about Oscar Pistorius&#8217;s girlfriend.</li>
<li>A <a href="//www.odditycentral.com/foods/home-delivered-airplane-food-is-actually-a-thing-in-germany.html">food delivery service</a> in Germany caters to people who happen to love airline food.</li>
<li>India is <a href="//www.biv.com/article/2014/10/got-milk-indias-dairy-market-largely-limits/">making it difficult</a> to sell into its dairy market.</li>
<li>France is revolting against Germany&#8217;s <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/business/rift-opens-among-eurozone-leaders-over-germanys-insistence-on-austerity.html">insistence on austerity</a>.</li>
<li>The International Monetary Fund <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-10-07/imf-explains-why-it-keeps-overestimating-growth">explains why</a> it keeps overestimating growth.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Labor Department <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/07/home-care-workers_n_5947618.html">plans to delay</a> its enforcement of new minimum wage and overtime protections for the country&#8217;s home care workers.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
